## 🚀 Introduction

The **7400 IC** is one of the most famous integrated circuits in digital electronics.

It contains **four independent 2-input NAND gates** and belongs to the **TTL (Transistor-Transistor Logic)** family.

> 💡 Since NAND is a **Universal Gate**, every other logic gate can be built using only NAND gates.

