## 🌍 Why is NAND Special?

NAND is called a **Universal Gate** because it can create:

* ✅ NOT
* ✅ AND
* ✅ OR
* ✅ NOR
* ✅ XOR
* ✅ XNOR

---

<details>
<summary>🔍 Click to See NAND Implementations</summary>

### NOT Gate

```text
A ----+
      |
      +---- NAND ---- Y
      |
A ----+
```

```text
Y = ¬A
```

### AND Gate

```text
Y = (A NAND B) NAND (A NAND B)
```

### OR Gate

```text
Y = (A NAND A) NAND (B NAND B)
```

</details>

